org.enhydra.shark.instancepersistence.dodsselective

Class DODSSelectivePersistenceManager

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.enhydra.shark.instancepersistence.dods.DODSPersistentManager
      • org.enhydra.shark.instancepersistence.dodsselective.DODSSelectivePersistenceManager
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    PersistentManagerInterface

    public class DODSSelectivePersistenceManager
extends org.enhydra.shark.instancepersistence.dods.DODSPersistentManager
    This DODS 'selective' implementation of InstancePersistence API checks for the extended attribute called 'Transient', and if it exists, it doesn't persist given process or its underlying objects.

    Another feature of this implementation is that it searches for the process definition extended attribute called 'DeleteFinished' which if exists overrides configuration settings for deleting finished processes.

    Version:
    1.0
    Author:
    Sasa Bojanic
